    "notes": "High-fidelity detection signal: mstsc.exe spawned by a process residing in a user-writable temp path (AppData\\Local\\Temp) is highly anomalous. Legitimate RDP is nearly always user-initiated from explorer.exe, a desktop shortcut (RunDLL), or an IT management tool installed in Program Files. Detections should alert on mstsc.exe where process.parent.executable matches Temp/AppData/Roaming paths. Secondary signal: .rdp file creation correlated with a non-interactive parent is a strong lateral movement indicator. Correlate the EID 1 (process create) → EID 3 (network conn) → EID 11 (file create) chain within a short time window for high-confidence alerting."
